07/14/2017 - Erik Wilkins * Updated COMPATIBLE option (RDBMS version of staging database) from 9 to 12
COMPONENT NAME: CKM Oracle
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - Check Knowledge Module for Oracle - This module controls the validity of the constraints of a Datastore and rejects the invalid records in an error table. It can be used for static controls as well as flow controls. - This module creates non unique index on the I$ table before checking AK and PK and an index on the E$ table before removing erroneous records from I$ table.
RESTRICTIONS - Data cleansing can be performed only if an update key is defined on the controlled table. - This Knowledge Module uses Oracle RowId column for data cleansing.
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option) - DROP_ERROR_TABLE: When this option is set to YES, the error table will be dropped each time a control is performed on the target table. This means that any rejected records, identified and stored during previous control operations, will be lost. - DROP_CHECK_TABLE: When this option is set to YES, the SNP_CHECK_TAB check table (which is created in the default Physical Schema of the Physical Server that hosts the controlled table) will be dropped each time a control is performed on the target table. This table contains a collection of all rejected records retrieved from all datastores hosted on the same Physical Server (whatever the Physical Schema may be). - UPGRADE_ERROR_TABLE: When this option is set to YES, the existing E$ table will be upgraded to the new E$ table structure.

When this option is set to YES, the error table will be dropped each time a control is performed on the target table. This means that any rejected records, identified and stored during previous control operations, will be lost.

When this option is set to YES, the SNP_CHECK_TAB check table (which is created in the default Physical Schema of the Physical Server that hosts the controlled table) will be dropped each time a control is performed on the target table. This table contains a collection of all rejected records retrieved from all datastores hosted on the same Physical Server (whatever the Physical Schema may be).
Create Index on the error table

set this Option to Yes for creating a non unique indexes on the Error table.
Note: When error table is not dropped at every execution (DROP_ERROR_TABLE=Yes), insert performance into error table may decrease due to this index.
This option enables/disables index creation on flow table.

This option affects the use of PURGE key word:
Values PURGE 10 Yes 9 No

This option generates an extra validation step during development. Validations performed are: - validation of KM option COMPATIBLE
This option should be turned off for all production use in particular for high-frequency execution. There is not added value in production, only processing overhead.
Note : Execute this this grant as sys to modify the permissions of the target data server schema
grant select on v_$parameter to <user>;

In case you use this CKM in an Oracle DB 11R2 or later environment with Editions activated and data is accessed through editioning views instead of directly through tables, you should consider activating this option. Please see KM reference guide for details.
When this option is set to YES, the existing E$ table and check tables will be dropped and recreate.

<% if (odiRef.getOption("ENABLE_EDITION_SUPPORT").equals("0")) { /* No edition support needed */ %> create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ODI_ROW_ID UROWID, ODI_ERR_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ODI_ERR_MESS <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ODI_CHECK_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE", "", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] " + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL"), ",\n\t", "", "")%>, ODI_ORIGIN <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ODI_CONS_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "128", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ODI_CONS_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "2", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ODI_PK <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "32", "")%> PRIMARY KEY, ODI_SESS_NO <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "36", "")%> ) <% } else { /* Edition support needed */ %> declare viewExists NUMBER(1,0); tableExists NUMBER(1,0); baseTableName VARCHAR2(100 CHAR); begin -- Check, if old non-EV-support error table already exists select count('X') into tableExists from ALL_TABLES where OWNER = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>' and TABLE_NAME = substr('<%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME","W")%>', length('<%=odiRef.getSchemaName("W")%>')+2);
-- Check, if error view already exists select count('X') into viewExists from ALL_EDITIONING_VIEWS_AE where owner = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>' and view_name = substr('<%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME","W")%>', length('<%=odiRef.getSchemaName("W")%>')+2);
-- Generate a GUID base table name <? String tableName = java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString().toUpperCase().replace('-','_'); ?> baseTableName := '<?=odiRef.getObjectName("L","%ERR_PRF"+tableName, "W")?>';
if tableExists > 0 then execute immediate 'alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> to '|| baseTableName; else begin execute immediate 'create table '|| baseTableName ||' '|| '( ' || ' ODI_ROW_ID UROWID, ' || ' ODI_ERR_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' ODI_ERR_MESS <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' ODI_CHECK_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE", "", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] " + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL"), ",\n\t", "", "")%>, ' || ' ODI_ORIGIN <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' ODI_CONS_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "128", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' ODI_CONS_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "2", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ' || ' ODI_PK <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "32", "")%> PRIMARY KEY, '|| ' ODI_SESS_NO <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "36", "")%>)'; end; end if;
-- Create EV view on Guid error table execute immediate 'create or replace view <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME","W")%> as ' || 'select ODI_ROW_ID, ODI_ERR_TYPE, ODI_ERR_MESS, ODI_CHECK_DATE, ' || '<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "")%>, ' || 'ODI_ORIGIN, ODI_CONS_NAME, ODI_CONS_TYPE,ODI_PK,ODI_SESS_NO ' || 'from '|| baseTableName ;
end;
<%};%>

insert /*+ APPEND_VALUES NO_GATHER_OPTIMIZER_STATISTICS */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ODI_PK, ODI_SESS_NO, ODI_ROW_ID, ODI_ERR_TYPE, ODI_ERR_MESS, ODI_CHECK_DATE, ODI_ORIGIN, ODI_CONS_NAME, ODI_CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> ) select SYS_GUID(), '<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>', rowid, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getCK("MESS")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', '<%=odiRef.getCK("COND_NAME")%>', 'CK', <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> <%=odiRef.getCK("COND_ALIAS")%> where not ( <%=odiRef.getCK("COND_SQL")%> ) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>

insert /*+ APPEND_VALUES NO_GATHER_OPTIMIZER_STATISTICS */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ODI_PK, ODI_SESS_NO, ODI_ROW_ID, ODI_ERR_TYPE, ODI_ERR_MESS, ODI_CHECK_DATE, ODI_ORIGIN, ODI_CONS_NAME, ODI_CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> ) select SYS_GUID(), '<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>', rowid, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getNotNullCol("MESS")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', '<%=odiRef.getSqlQuotedString(odiRef.getNotNullCol("COL_NAME"))%>', 'NN', <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> where <%=odiRef.getNotNullCol("COL_NAME")%> is null <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>

delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> T where exists ( select 1 from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where ODI_SESS_NO = '<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>' and T.rowid = E.ODI_ROW_ID )
insert check sum into check table

insert /*+ APPEND NO_GATHER_OPTIMIZER_STATISTICS */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME", "W")%> ( SCHEMA_NAME, RESOURCE_NAME, FULL_RES_NAME, ERR_TYPE, ERR_MESS, CHECK_DATE, ORIGIN, CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE, ERR_COUNT ) select '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("SCHEMA")%>', '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME")%>', '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%>', E.ODI_ERR_TYPE, E.ODI_ERR_MESS, E.ODI_CHECK_DATE, E.ODI_ORIGIN, E.ODI_CONS_NAME, E.ODI_CONS_TYPE, count(1) from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where E.ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' and E.ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' group by E.ODI_ERR_TYPE, E.ODI_ERR_MESS, E.ODI_CHECK_DATE, E.ODI_ORIGIN, E.ODI_CONS_NAME, E.ODI_CONS_TYPE

delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> where (ODI_ERR_TYPE = 'S' and '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' = 'S') or (ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' and ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>')

insert/*+ APPEND NO_GATHER_OPTIMIZER_STATISTICS */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ODI_PK, ODI_SESS_NO, ODI_ROW_ID, ODI_ERR_TYPE, ODI_ERR_MESS, ODI_ORIGIN, ODI_CHECK_DATE, ODI_CONS_NAME, ODI_CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "MAP")%> ) select SYS_GUID(), '<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>', rowid, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getPK("MESS")%>', '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getPK("KEY_NAME")%>', 'PK', <%=odiRef.getColList("", odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")+".[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> <%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")%> where <%=odiRef.getColList("(", odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")+".[COL_NAME]", ",", ")", "PK")%> IN ( select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "SUB.[COL_NAME]", ",
			", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CT_NAME","A")%> SUB group by <%=odiRef.getColList("", "SUB.[COL_NAME]", ",
			", "", "PK")%> having count(1) > 1 ) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>

insert /*+ APPEND_VALUES NO_GATHER_OPTIMIZER_STATISTICS */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ODI_PK, ODI_SESS_NO, ODI_ROW_ID, ODI_ERR_TYPE, ODI_ERR_MESS, ODI_ORIGIN, ODI_CHECK_DATE, ODI_CONS_NAME, ODI_CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "MAP")%> ) select SYS_GUID(), '<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>', rowid, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getAK("MESS")%>', '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getAK("KEY_NAME")%>', 'AK', <%=odiRef.getColList("", odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")+".[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> <%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")%> where <%=odiRef.getAKColList("(", odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_ALIAS")+".[COL_NAME]", ",", ")")%> IN ( select <%=odiRef.getAKColList("", "SUB.[COL_NAME]", ",
			", "")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CT_NAME","A")%> SUB group by <%=odiRef.getAKColList("", "SUB.[COL_NAME]", ",
			", "")%> having count(1) > 1 ) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>

<% if (odiRef.getOption("ENABLE_EDITION_SUPPORT").equals("0")) { 
/* No edition support needed */ %>
drop table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <% if (new Integer(odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )).intValue() >= 10 ) { out.print( "purge" ); }; %>
<% } else { 
/* Edition support needed */
%>
declare
	viewExists	NUMBER(1,0);
	tableExists	NUMBER(1,0);
	baseTableName	VARCHAR2(100 CHAR);
begin	
	-- Check, if old non-EV-support error table already exists
	select 	count('X') 
	into	tableExists
	from 	ALL_TABLES
	where 	OWNER = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>'
	and		TABLE_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%>';
	
	if tableExists > 0 then
		begin
			execute immediate 'drop table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> purge';
		end;
	else
		begin
			-- Check, if error view already exists
			select 	count('X') 
			into	viewExists
			from 	ALL_VIEWS 
			where 	OWNER = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>'
			and		VIEW_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%>';
			
			if viewExists > 0 then
				begin
					select	OWNER||'.'||TABLE_NAME
					into 	baseTableName
					from 	ALL_EDITIONING_VIEWS_AE
					where 	OWNER = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>'
					and		VIEW_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%>'
					and		EDITION_NAME = sys_context('userenv', 'current_edition_name');
					
					execute immediate 'drop table '|| baseTableName ||' purge';
					execute immediate 'drop view <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ';
				end;
			end if;
		end;
	end if;
end;	
<%};%>

<% if (odiRef.getOption("ENABLE_EDITION_SUPPORT").equals("0")){ /* No Editioning View Support */ %> create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%> ( CATALOG_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , SCHEMA_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , RESOURCE_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, FULL_RES_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_MESS <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , CHECK_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE", "", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ORIGIN <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, CONS_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "128", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, CONS_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "2", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "10", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> ) <% } else { /* Editioning View support enabled */ %>
DECLARE
oldtableExists NUMBER(1,0); newtableExists NUMBER(1,0);
BEGIN
-- Check, if old non-EV-support check table already exists select count('X') into oldtableExists from all_tables where owner = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>' and table_name = substr('<%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>', length('<%=odiRef.getSchemaName("W")%>')+2);
-- Check, if EV-support check table already exists select count('X') into newtableExists from all_tables where owner = '<%=odiRef.getSchemaNameDefaultPSchema("W")%>' and table_name = substr('<%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>', length('<%=odiRef.getSchemaName("W")%>')+2)||'_AE';
IF oldtableExists > 0 THEN -- Auto-Upgrade from previous setup with ENABLE_EDITION_SUPPORT=No execute immediate 'alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%> add EDITION_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "30", "0" )%> default sys_context(''userenv'', ''current_edition_name'')'; execute immediate 'alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%> to substr(''<%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>'', length(''<%=odiRef.getSchemaName("W")%>'')+2)_AE'; ELSIF newtableExists = 0 THEN -- Create table execute immediate 'create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>_AE (' || ' EDITION_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "30", "0" )%> default sys_context(''userenv'', ''current_edition_name''),' || ' CATALOG_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' SCHEMA_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> ,' || ' RESOURCE_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' FULL_RES_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' ERR_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' ERR_MESS <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> ,' || ' CHECK_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE", "", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' ORIGIN <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' CONS_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "128", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' CONS_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "2", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>,' || ' ERR_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "10", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>' || ' )'; END IF;
-- Create view returning only check records of current edition execute immediate 'create or replace view <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%> as' || ' select EDITION_NAME, CATALOG_NAME, SCHEMA_NAME, RESOURCE_NAME, FULL_RES_NAME, ERR_TYPE, ERR_MESS, CHECK_DATE, ORIGIN, CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE, ERR_COUNT' || ' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>_AE' || ' where EDITION_NAME = sys_context(''userenv'', ''current_edition_name'')'; END; <% }; %>
